{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"fozy-vermiform-lemming","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## What\nAn OPTIONAL, isolated adapter that harvests coverage % and CI-health (status, duration, red->green recovery, flake/recheck rate) from GitHub Actions run history within the retention window, and hardens coverage by writing it to the going-forward snapshot so it stops depending on log retention. The core command does not depend on this adapter.\n\n## Files\n- `src/rebar/metrics/adapters/github_actions.py` — new isolated adapter over `gh`/the Actions API.\n- `scripts/harvest_gha.py` — new: pull `test.yml` coverage totals + workflow-run outcomes into labeled snapshots.\n- `.github/workflows/test.yml` — append the current coverage % to the snapshot store on each run (going-forward hardening; a step, not a new trigger).\n- `tests/unit/metrics/test_gha_adapter.py` — new.\n\n## Approach\nCI runs on GitHub Actions; coverage is in the `test.yml` run-log tail and CI-health in the run metadata, but only within a short retention window — so we harvest the window as a seed AND persist coverage forward via the snapshot so history accrues durably. To keep the harness portable, the CI source is an isolated adapter the core command never imports; a parallel adapter could target another CI. Log parsing is anchored (word-boundary grep for the coverage TOTAL line). The `test.yml` edit adds only a step under the existing push/PR triggers (no new git-ref/event trigger).\n\n## Tests\n- Unit (fixture log text + run-metadata JSON): the adapter extracts the coverage % from a fixture log tail and computes a red->green recovery interval from two fixture runs; output carries the snapshot label.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `tests/unit/metrics/test_gha_adapter.py` passes: a fixture `test.yml` log yields the parsed coverage % (`assert pct == 84.2`) and two fixture runs (fail then pass) yield the expected recovery duration.\n- [ ] the portability guard holds: a unit test asserts the core command does not import the GHA adapter.\n- [ ] the `test.yml` change appends coverage to `reports/metrics-snapshots.ndjson` — a workflow-lint/test asserts the added step targets the snapshot store.","id":"1f77-f8c0-bfae-4a79","parent_id":"86ac-086a-20ad-4327","priority":2,"tags":["metrics","backfill"],"ticket_type":"task","title":"GitHub-Actions coverage + CI-health harvest adapter (optional, isolated)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784416860225678001,"uuid":"21347ded-6806-4b04-9606-d2e7879935c9"}